text:
'Cangjie programming language_enum_type_enum_definition': 'In Cangjie code language, Enums in Cangjie are defined using the enum keyword, followed by the enum name and a body enclosed in curly braces. The body contains a list of constructors separated by |. Each constructor represents a possible value of the enum type.'

Code_Example:
enum RGBColor {
    | Red | Green | Blue
}

'Cangjie programming language_enum_type_enum_multiple_constructors': 'In Cangjie code language, Cangjie allows multiple constructors with the same name in an enum, as long as they have different numbers of parameters.'

Code_Example:
enum RGBColor {
    | Red | Green | Blue
    | Red(UInt8) | Green(UInt8) | Blue(UInt8)
}

'Cangjie programming language_enum_type_enum_members': 'In Cangjie code language, Enums can also define member functions, operator functions, and properties within their body. Constructors, member functions, and properties must not have the same name.'

Code_Example:
enum RGBColor {
    | Red | Green | Blue


    public static func printType() {
        print("RGBColor")
    }
}

'Cangjie programming language_enum_type_enum_usage': 'In Cangjie code language, After defining an enum, you can create instances of the enum type by using the constructors. Enum values are created using the type name followed by the constructor, or directly using the constructor if there is no ambiguity.'

Code_Example:
enum RGBColor {
    | Red | Green | Blue(UInt8)
}
main() {
    let r = RGBColor.Red
    let g = Green
    let b = Blue(100)
}

'Cangjie programming language_enum_type_enum_name_conflicts': 'In Cangjie code language, When omitting a type name, the name of the enum constructor may conflict with the type name, variable name, or function name. In this case, you must add the enum type name to use the enum constructor, otherwise only the type, variable, and function definition with the same name will be selected.'

Code_Example:
let Red = 1
func Green(g: UInt8) {
    return g
}
enum RGBColor {
    | Red | Green(UInt8) | Blue(UInt8)
}
let r1 = Red                 // Will choose 'let Red'
let r2 = RGBColor.Red        // Ok: constructed by enum type name
let g1 = Green(100)          // Will choose 'func Green'
let g2 = RGBColor.Green(100) // Ok: constructed by enum type name
let b = Blue(100)            // Ok: can be uniquely identified as an enum constructor

Error_case_code:
class Blue {}
enum RGBColor {
    | Red | Green(UInt8) | Blue(UInt8)
}
let b = Blue(100)           // Will choose constructor of 'class Blue' and report an error
